MILL Mobile App Development Strategy
Project Overview
We are developing a mobile application that provides comprehensive access to Indian land laws. The 
app will feature a fullscreen map of India, law searching and browsing capabilities, historical context, 
user engagement features, and advanced legal research tools.
Target features:
1. Access and Navigation
1.1. Homepage with an overview of the app's features 
1.2. Search functionality for specific land laws using keywords 
1.3. Filter search results by law category (e.g., property rights, land acquisition) 
1.4. Browse laws by historical periods (pre-colonial, post-colonial) 
1.5. Language switch between English and regional languages 
1.6. Display related laws and documents when viewing a specific act 
1.7. Clean, readable format for viewing laws 
1.8. Download laws for offline reading
2. Historical Context
2.1. Historical timelines related to land laws 
2.2. Access to historical documents and archives
3. User Engagement
3.1. Basic notifications for updates on land laws
4. User Interface and Experience
4.1. Clean and intuitive app layout 
4.2. Easy navigation between sections of the app 
4.3. Quick access to recent searches and viewed documents 
4.4. Dark mode for reading in low light 
4.5. Adjustable text size for better readability
5. Legal Research Tools
5.1. Keyword searches within laws and documents 
5.2. Advanced search filters (e.g., by date, region) 
5.3. Track changes and updates in legal documents 
5.4. View summaries and highlights of complex legal documents
6. Integration and Connectivity
6.1. Share documents and findings via email or social media
