Development Strategy
Phase 1: Core Functionality
1. Set up React Native project with TypeScript for type safety
2. Implement user authentication with Firebase
3. Develop the homepage and basic navigation structure
4. Integrate Mapbox GL Native for the fullscreen map feature
5. Set up Algolia for full-text search of laws
6. Implement basic law viewing functionality
Phase 2: Advanced Features
1. Develop filtering and advanced search capabilities
2. Implement offline mode for downloaded laws using Redux Persist
3. Create historical timelines using Victory Native
4. Integrate i18next for multi-language support
5. Implement document sharing functionality
6. Develop user preferences (e.g., text size, dark mode)
Phase 3: User Experience and Performance
1. Refine UI/UX based on user feedback
2. Implement push notifications for law updates
3. Optimize app performance, especially for large datasets
4. Enhance accessibility features
5. Implement analytics to track user behavior and app performance
Phase 4: Legal Research Tools
1. Develop keyword search within documents
2. Implement change tracking for legal documents
3. Create a system for summarizing and highlighting complex documents
4. Integrate historical document archives
Phase 5: Testing, Security, and Deployment
1. Conduct thorough testing (unit, integration, user acceptance)
2. Perform security audit, especially for handling sensitive legal data
3. Optimize for app store requirements
4. Prepare for deployment to iOS App Store and Google Play Store
